<p>Michael Jackson was born on August 29, 1958, in Gary, Indiana, USA. He was the eighth of ten children in the Jackson family, a working-class African-American family. Michael began his music career at a young age, performing with his older brothers in a group called The Jackson 5. The group became successful in the late 1960s and early 1970s, with hits like "I Want You Back," "ABC," and "I'll Be There."</p><p><br /></p><p>In 1971, Michael began his solo career while still a member of The Jackson 5. His early solo hits included "Got to Be There" and "Ben." However, it was in the late 1970s and 1980s that Michael Jackson truly became a global superstar. His 1979 album "Off the Wall," produced by Quincy Jones, was a critical and commercial success, featuring hits like "Don't Stop 'Til You Get Enough" and "Rock with You."</p><p><br /></p><p>In 1982, Michael released "Thriller," which became the best-selling album of all time. The album included iconic tracks like "Billie Jean," "Beat It," and the title track "Thriller," which was accompanied by a groundbreaking music video that showcased Michael's dance moves and storytelling abilities. The "Thriller" music video set new standards for the music video industry and cemented Michael's status as the "King of Pop."</p><p><br /></p><p>Throughout the 1980s and 1990s, Michael continued to release successful albums, including "Bad" (1987), "Dangerous" (1991), and "HIStory: Past, Present and Future, Book I" (1995). He was known for his distinctive voice, innovative music videos, and signature dance moves, including the moonwalk, which became one of his trademarks.</p><p><br /></p><p>Michael Jackson was also known for his humanitarian work, donating millions of dollars to various charities and causes throughout his life. He was deeply committed to making the world a better place, as reflected in songs like "We Are the World" (which he co-wrote with Lionel Richie) and "Heal the World."</p><p><br /></p><p>However, Michael's life was also marked by controversy. He faced multiple allegations of child sexual abuse, which he denied. In 2005, he was acquitted of all charges in a highly publicized trial. Despite these controversies, Michael's influence on music, dance, and popular culture remained undeniable.</p><p><br /></p><p>Michael Jackson passed away on June 25, 2009, at the age of 50, due to acute propofol and benzodiazepine intoxication, which led to cardiac arrest. His death was ruled a homicide, and his personal physician, Dr. Conrad Murray, was later convicted of involuntary manslaughter.</p><p><br /></p><p>Michael Jackson's legacy as one of the greatest entertainers in history continues to live on. His music, videos, and philanthropic efforts have left an indelible mark on the world, and he remains an icon of pop culture.</p>
